  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Overall goal: Let's re-design the front-end of the edit profile page to create a more pleasant user 
experience. The current edit profile page is aesthetically un-appealing, time-consuming to 
complete, and has CSS flaws.

Even though I'm not a designer or artist, I can see room for improvement on this page. 

There are some obvious glaring CSS flaws that should really be fixed, as shown in the attached 
screenshot: 
1. the instructional text don't line up in the same line 
2 the save and cancel button are not on the same line 
 
Some design-related proposals: 
1. Most of the instructional text are located on the right side of the box. Instead, I think the page 
looks better if the text are placed directly above the form boxes or are used as text placeholders 
within the box itself. 
2. The page looks long and time-consuming to complete, which is possibly bad for bounce rate 
and user engagement. We can shorten the page by reducing the size of the form boxes. 

I'm free to discuss with anyone interested in design stuff as it relates to this ticket on IRC. My nick 
is ArcTanSusan.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
